 Port Elizabeth - The Coega Development Corporation (CDC) will from next week, 09-17 September 2019 embark on stakeholder roadshows in the Nelson Mandela Bay Municipality (NMBM) region to inform, educate and empower communities and small businesses. The focus of the roadshows will be on jobs, Small Medium Micro Enterprise (SMME) support and development, training and development, and Corporate Social Responsibility (CSR) initiatives. “The roadshows form part of our Coega’s outreach programmes, which takes place on regular bases every year throughout the province of the Eastern Cape starting in the NMBM.” says, Dr Ayanda Vilakazi, CDC unit head of marketing & communications. The roadshows will take place at the following listed venues: Nelson Mandela Bay Uitenhage Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 